        <title>Zoom Captions Settings for Accessibility</title>
        <published>2024-10-17T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2025-10-21T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://asyaplugged.in/know/zoom-captions/"/>
        <id>https://asyaplugged.in/know/zoom-captions/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://asyaplugged.in/know/zoom-captions/">&lt;h2 id=&quot;why-captions-matter&quot;&gt;Why Captions Matter&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Zoom has a built-in closed captioning function that can make meetings accessible for people with hearing and learning disabilities, but it requires meeting leaders to turn them on manually in the extended browser settings.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;step-1-enable-captioning-in-browser-settings&quot;&gt;Step 1: Enable Captioning in Browser Settings&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to your &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;zoom.us&#x2F;profile&#x2F;setting?tab=meeting&quot;&gt;Zoom Settings → Meeting tab&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scroll all the way down to &lt;strong&gt;In Meeting (Advanced)&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Toggle &lt;strong&gt;Closed Captioning&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;Save Captions&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; to &lt;strong&gt;ON&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make sure both &lt;strong&gt;Allow use of Caption API&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Enable Live Transcription&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; are checked — this allows subtitles to appear in a sidebar that remains visible after something is said.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enabling &lt;strong&gt;Save Captions&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; is useful for post-meeting note-taking. If it is not enabled, meeting participants can still take screenshots of the sidebar, so it&#x27;s a kind gesture to toggle it on.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;toggle.png&quot; alt=&quot;screenshot of zoom settings&quot; &gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;step-2-turn-on-captions-during-a-meeting&quot;&gt;Step 2: Turn On Captions During a Meeting&lt;&#x2F;h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once your meeting starts, click the &lt;strong&gt;CC&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; icon in the meeting control bar.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select &lt;strong&gt;Enable Auto-Transcription&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;.&lt;br &#x2F;&gt;
This will activate both live closed captions and a transcript sidebar. You can also save the transcript automatically if the meeting is recorded.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;CC-button.png&quot; alt=&quot;screenshot of CC button in zoom window&quot; &gt;
&lt;p&gt;Congratulations, you&#x27;re done. Now your meeting is accessible!&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
